`agents/` is a single-file directory: one reference adapter (`summarizer-claude.py`) implementing the external agent contract that the Rust pipeline invokes via `CTX_AGENT_CMD`. Its job in the system is to be the default, working implementation of that contract and the template for anyone writing an alternative backend (e.g. a different model provider or a mock for testing).

There's no cross-file coupling to describe since there's only one child — the invariants worth restating at this level are the ones that define the *contract surface* any future sibling adapter must also satisfy: stdin is `{"system": str, "user": str}` JSON, stdout is raw completion text and nothing else, non-zero exit with stderr message on any failure, and no exit path that swallows an error silently. Anything implementing `CTX_AGENT_CMD` differently than this breaks the runner.

A typical change here is either swapping model/provider specifics (env vars, endpoint, payload shape) or adding a new adapter file alongside this one — in the latter case, the stdin/stdout contract above is the one thing that must not drift between them.

No intent.md exists to check against.